osals above a basic threshold must be routed through a centralized credit risk assessment committee at the head office.3. Conclusion:\n\nIn conclusion, aggressive network expansion without robust administrative guardrails inevitably leads to a governance breakdown. By combining structural decentralization with automated digital monitoring and rigorous audit compliance, Western Banking House can successfully regain full control over its remote branches, safeguarding its reputation as a premier banking institution."
