e, and maintains macroeconomic stability.5. Conclusion:\n\nIn conclusion, the strategic choice made by 'X' Bank (the Central Bank) was highly rational and functional. By scaling up its open market asset purchases, the bank successfully pumped needed liquidity into the monetary framework, optimized credit velocity, and established complete stability across the national money market."
