                                                "answer": "Para 1: Identification\n\nBased on organizational structure and geographical operation, the 'Apex Bank' mentioned in the stem is a Unit Bank.\n\n\nPara 2: Theoretical Explanation\n\nA unit bank is a specialized form of banking system where an institution conducts all of its financial operations and commercial activities strictly within a single, localized office or a highly confined geographic boundary. Unlike branch banking systems, a unit bank does not possess a widespread network of branches; its management, decision-making, and customer service desks are entirely centralized and self-contained within that lone facility, making its operational scale highly localized.\n\n\nPara 3: Contextual Application\n\nThe stem specifies that Apex Bank conducts its entire banking operations through \"only a single office.\" Because it lacks external branch desks, Ms. Bhavna runs into severe geographical constraints when trying to clear invoices, receive vendor payments, or coordinate remote logistics for her digital market setup. Since the bank operates out of one centralized brick-and-mortar location without any external networks, it perfectly matches the structural definition of a unit bank."
