                                                "answer": "Para 1: Core Concept\n\nA garnishee order is a statutory legal decree issued by a court of law directing a bank to freeze or attach a debtor's bank account to secure funds for paying off an outstanding judgment debt owed to a creditor.\n\n\nPara 2: Underlying Purpose and Process\n\nThe primary reason for issuing a garnishee order is to enforce legal accountability on a defaulting debtor who possesses financial balances but refuses to settle their judicially declared dues. When a creditor files an enforcement petition, the court serves this mandate to the debtor's bank. Upon receipt, the bank is legally obligated to suspend all withdrawal transactions and cheque clearings from that specific account up to the designated liability limit, acting as a custodian until the frozen cash is formally transferred to liquidate the creditor's valid claim."
