                                                "label": "d",
                                                "text": "\"Ekota Bank is more helpful than Dokhota Bank in expanding trade and commerce\"—Do you agree with this statement? Give your opinion.",
                                                "answer": "Para 1: Decisive Opinion\n\nYes, I completely agree with the statement. For an expanding business with a countrywide market reach, a branch banking system like Ekota Bank is vastly more effective and supportive than a single-office unit bank like Dokhota Bank.\n\n\nPara 2: Explaining Branch Banking Advantages\n\nBranch banking allows a large financial institution to deploy thousands of customer desks nationwide under a single corporate brand and unified management. For modern entrepreneurs, this setup functions as a widespread financial pipeline that facilitates fast inter-branch domestic remittances, localized document clearing, real-time online fund routing, and massive overdraft capacities that are vital for sustaining long-distance business operations.\n\n\nPara 3: Contextual Justification\n\nMr. Shakil's business grew from a localized setup into a countrywide trade network, requiring him to process collections and make vendor payments across different districts. Dokhota Bank, being a unit bank limited to one office, could not handle fast remote settlements, causing clear operational friction. By opening an account with Ekota Bank, which \"provides banking services all over the country\" via its extensive branch framework, Shakil can instantly receive payments from remote buyers, access centralized corporate credit lines, and utilize real-time online banking facilities near any of his domestic clients.\n\n\nPara 4: Points of Strategic Synthesis\n\nThe superior helpfulness of Ekota Bank can be summarized through these core points:\n\n* Rapid Capital Mobility: Ekota Bank's nationwide branch footprint eliminates geographic delays, letting Shakil collect sales revenues from remote corners instantly via core banking systems.\n\n* Facilitation of Credit: Unlike small unit banks that face local capital limitations, large branch banks like Ekota Bank have vast loanable funds to finance large-scale corporate expansions.\n\n* Reduction in Transaction Costs: Dealing with branches of the same bank reduces inter-bank agency fees and clearing delays for drafts and cheques, streamlining supply chain liquidity. Therefore, Ekota Bank is undeniably more helpful for trade expansion."
