                                "answer": "Fraud and forgery of a cheque refer to illegal and deceptive acts where a cheque is altered, faked, or manipulated with dishonest intent. Forgery specifically involves duplicating someone else's signature or altering vital instrument details (like the amount or payee name) without authorization, while fraud includes intentionally issuing a cheque knowing there are no funds available.These activities are serious financial crimes aimed at unlawfully draining an account holder's wealth or cheating a business party. To combat this, banking laws impose rigid verification protocols, making drawers and banks highly vigilant about protecting checkbooks and validating signatures before executing any clearance."
