                        {
                                "id": "fin2-ch6-cq-015",
                                "category": "Knowledge",
                                "question": "What is a central bank?",
                                "answer": "A central bank is the supreme, independent financial institution of a country that acts as the guardian of the money market, controls the money supply and credit system, and regulates all commercial banking operations for economic stability."
