                                "category": "Comprehension",
                                "question": "Write down the reasons for the dishonor/rejection of a cheque.",
                                "answer": "A cheque can be rejected or dishonored by bank authorities for several technical, legal, and structural reasons. The most common grounds include:1. Insufficient Funds: The account balance of the drawer is less than the amount written on the cheque leaf.\n\n2. Signature Mismatch: The drawer's signature on the cheque does not match the official record stored on the specimen signature card.\n\n3. Stale or Post-Dated Instrument: Presenting the cheque after its statutory 6-month (180 days) validity has expired, or presenting it before the date written on its face.\n\n4. Mismatched Amounts: A clear discrepancy between the amount specified in numbers and the amount written in words.\n\n5. Overwriting or Alterations: Any corrections or overwriting on critical sections (date, name, or amount) without the drawer's clarifying counter-signature."
