                                                "answer": "A stale cheque (বাসি চেক) is a cheque that is presented to the bank after its statutory validity period has expired. According to standard banking laws and practices in Bangladesh, a cheque remains legally valid for exactly 6 months (180 days) from the date of issue written on the instrument.If a holder fails to present the cheque to the bank within this 6-month window, the cheque loses its commercial negotiability, and the bank is legally obligated to dishonor it. To get paid after a cheque becomes stale, the holder must approach the drawer to either alter and re-sign the date or issue a brand new cheque."
