                                                "label": "a",
                                                "text": "What is a specimen signature card?",
                                                "answer": "A specimen signature card is a card containing the official, verified signatures of an account holder that a bank collects at the time of account opening and keeps on record to cross-check and verify future withdrawal transactions."
                                        },
                                        {
                                                "label": "b",
                                                "text": "Why does a bank maintain account confidentiality? Explain.",
                                                "answer": "A bank maintains strict account confidentiality to protect the privacy, financial security, and personal safety of its customers, as well as to preserve institutional trust. If financial information is leaked, it exposes customers to severe operational vulnerabilities like targeted theft, fraud, blackmail, or unfair competitive disadvantages in the marketplace.Furthermore, commercial banks are bound by strict legal, ethical, and statutory regulations to keep asset balances and transactional details completely confidential. Violating this fiduciary duty damages the bank's reputation, whereas maintaining robust secrecy ensures a stable and trustworthy relationship between the public and the financial system."
                                        },
