                                "stem": "Mr. Khan executed insurance contracts with two companies, 'Popular' and 'Green', for a factory. In an accident, property worth 1 lakh BDT in Mr. Khan's factory was damaged. According to the contract, both companies jointly paid Mr. Khan a total compensation of 1 lakh BDT at an equal rate. Later, Mr. Khan sold the damaged property for 20,000 BDT. Upon hearing the news, both companies presented a claim on this sale price.",
                                "stemImage": "",
                                "meta": "Sylhet Board · 2025",
                                "type": "board",
                                "questions": [
                                        {
                                                "label": "a",
                                                "text": "What is insurance?",
                                                "answer": "Insurance is a legal contract where one party (the insurer) agrees to compensate another party (the insured) for a specific loss or damage in exchange for a fee called a premium."
                                        },
                                        {
                                                "label": "b",
                                                "text": "What is meant by insurable interest?",
                                                "answer": "Insurable interest means the legal right of the insured to insure an object or life because they have a financial relationship with it and would suffer a monetary loss if it were damaged."
                                        },
                                        {
                                                "label": "c",
                                                "text": "In light of which principle of the insurance contract did both companies provide compensation to Mr. Khan? Explain.",
                                                "answer": "Data: Two companies, Popular and Green, shared the 1 lakh BDT loss \"at an equal rate.\" <br> Analysis: When the same risk is insured with multiple insurers, they share the loss proportionately so the insured doesn't profit. This is the 'Principle of Contribution'. <br> Conclusion: The companies paid him based on the 'Principle of Contribution'."
                                        },
                                        {
                                                "label": "d",
                                                "text": "Evaluate the logic of both companies' claim on the sale price of the damaged property.",
                                                "answer": "Data: The insurers paid the full 1 lakh loss, but Mr. Khan kept the 20,000 BDT from the scrap sale. <br> Analysis: According to the 'Principle of Subrogation', once the insurer pays the full compensation, the rights to the salvage (wreckage) pass to the insurer. <br> Evaluation: If Mr. Khan keeps the money, he would receive 1.2 lakh for a 1 lakh loss, violating the Principle of Indemnity. <br> Decision: The companies' claim is logical. Legally, the sale proceeds belong to the insurers to prevent the insured from profiting."
                                        }
                                ]
                        },
                        {
                                "id": "fin2-ch10-cq-149",
