                                                "text": "What is insurance?",
                                                "answer": "Insurance is a contract of indemnity (except for life insurance) where the insurer promises to make good the loss of the insured in exchange for a premium."
                                        },
                                        {
                                                "label": "b",
                                                "text": "Why is insurance important for the expansion of international trade? Explain.",
                                                "answer": "Insurance is vital for international trade because it covers high-risk maritime perils (like shipwrecks or piracy), providing financial security to exporters and importers, which encourages them to engage in large-scale global commerce."
