                                                "label": "c",
                                                "text": "What type of insurance policy did Mr. Karim take in the stem? Explain.",
                                                "answer": "Data: Mr. Karim insured his \"ship\" (MV Surma) for a specific amount. <br> Analysis: Insurance that covers ships, cargo, or freight against perils of the sea is known as Marine Insurance. <br> Conclusion: Mr. Karim took a 'Marine Insurance' policy."
                                        },
                                        {
                                                "label": "d",
                                                "text": "Analyze the logic of the subsequent decision taken by 'XYZ' Insurance Company in the stem.",
                                                "answer": "Data: XYZ Company insured a portion (one-third) of their risk with another company, PQR. <br> Analysis: When an insurance company transfers a portion of its accepted risk to another insurance company to protect itself from a heavy loss, it is called 'Re-insurance'. <br> Evaluation: This allows XYZ to manage its liability and remain solvent in case of a massive claim. <br> Decision: The decision is highly logical. Re-insurance ensures financial stability for the primary insurer and helps them handle risks beyond their individual capacity."
                                        }
                                ]
                        },
                        {
                                "id": "fin2-ch10-cq-150",
                                "stem": "Mr. Rifat insured his personal private car for 25 lakh BDT with 'Fuel Insurance Company'. The car was completely damaged in an accident on the Dhaka-Chittagong highway. Subsequently, when Mr. Rifat presented an insurance claim, the insurance company paid the full amount. Later, the insurance company sold the damaged car for 4 lakh BDT and kept the entire amount. However, when Mr. Rifat claimed the money obtained from selling the damaged car, the insurance company refused to pay.",
