                                "type": "board",
                                "questions": [
                                        {
                                                "label": "a",
                                                "text": "What is the Principle of Subrogation?",
                                                "answer": "The Principle of Subrogation states that once the insurer pays the full compensation for a loss, they acquire all legal rights and ownership of the damaged property (salvage) from the insured."
                                        },
                                        {
                                                "label": "b",
                                                "text": "Why is insurance called a joint system of risk distribution? Explain.",
