                                                "answer": "Data: The policy pays if Mamun \"dies within the term\" OR \"at the end of the term\" to himself. <br> Analysis: A life insurance policy that pays the sum assured either upon death or after a fixed period (whichever comes first) is called an 'Endowment Policy'. <br> Conclusion: Mr. Mamun took an 'Endowment Life Insurance Policy'."
