                                "question": "What is reinsurance?",
                                "answer": "Reinsurance is a mechanism where an insurance company (the primary insurer) transfers a portion of its corporate risk exposure from an existing policy to another insurance company (the reinsurer) to safeguard its financial stability against massive claims."
