                                "category": "Comprehension",
                                "question": "What is meant by surrender value?",
                                "answer": "Surrender value (সমর্পণ মূল্য) refers to the specific cash amount that a life insurance company pays to a policyholder if they voluntarily terminate or cancel their policy before its official maturity date.When a policyholder stops paying premiums after a minimum required period (usually 2 to 3 years), the policy does not lapse completely; instead, it accumulates a cash value. The surrender value is calculated as a percentage of the total premiums paid, allowing the policyholder to recover a portion of their investment in exchange for forfeiting all future insurance coverage benefits."
                        },
