                                "answer": "A single life insurance policy (একক জীবন বিমাপত্র) refers to a life insurance contract issued to cover the risk on the life of only one specific individual.Under this policy, the premium amount is calculated based solely on the age, health condition, and risk profile of that single insured person. The sum assured becomes payable by the insurance company either upon the maturity of the term or upon the death of that particular individual, making it distinct from joint life policies that cover multiple people simultaneously."
                        },
