                                "answer": "A wagering contract (বাজি চুক্তি) is a speculative agreement where two parties hold opposite views on the outcome of an uncertain future event, agreeing that one will pay a specific sum of money to the other depending on how that event turns out.In a wagering contract, neither party has any real, lawful interest in the event itself other than the stake they stand to win or lose. Because it relies purely on chance, gambling mechanics, and lacks a legal insurable interest, a wagering contract is declared completely void and unenforceable under the Contract Act, 1872."
