                                "category": "Comprehension",
                                "question": "Why is insurance called a joint mechanism for risk distribution? Explain.",
                                "answer": "Insurance is called a joint mechanism for risk distribution (ঝুঁকি বণ্টনের যৌথ ব্যবস্থা) because it pools together small premium contributions from a large number of people exposed to similar risks to compensate for the actual financial losses suffered by a few individuals.Under this collaborative framework, the total financial burden of an unfortunate catastrophic event does not fall heavily on a single person or family. Instead, the collective premium fund accumulated from the entire group is used to absorb the shock, effectively distributing individual financial risks across a broad base of policyholders."
