                                "question": "\"Endowment life insurance acts as a tool for savings\"—Explain.",
                                "answer": "Endowment life insurance acts as an effective tool for savings because, unlike pure term insurance, it combines financial protection with a compulsory savings mechanism.Under an endowment policy, the policyholder pays regular premiums over a fixed period. If the insured survives the specified term, the insurance company returns the entire sum assured along with accumulated bonuses or profits. This guaranteed payout upon maturity encourages a disciplined savings habit, helping individuals accumulate a large lump-sum fund for future needs while remaining covered against life risks."
