                                                "answer": "The life insurance policy taken out by Mr. Maruf in the stem is a \"Term Insurance Policy\" (সাময়িক বিমাপত্র).According to insurance principles, a term insurance policy is a short-term contract that provides financial risk coverage for a very specific, limited duration of time (such as a few months or a year). The core operational feature of this policy is that the sum assured is paid strictly if the insured passes away within that specified window; if they survive the term smoothly, the policy naturally expires without returning any maturity value. Because it lacks savings elements, its premium rate is exceptionally low.In the given stem, Mr. Maruf took out a policy specifically to cover his high-risk deployment to Haiti for one year and successfully renewed it upon his safe return. Since the policy was bound to a strict, short-term risk window (one year) and carried a very low premium rate, it perfectly satisfies all criteria of a term insurance policy."
                                        },
                                        {
                                                "label": "d",
                                                "text": "\"Although the premium rate is high, Mr. Sumon will get more benefits\"—Evaluate the validity of this statement.",
                                                "answer": "1. Evaluation of the Statement:\n\nThe statement that \"Mr. Sumon will get more benefits despite a higher premium rate\" is entirely accurate, logical, and highly justified from a long-term financial security perspective. The difference lies in the contrast between short-term pure risk coverage and a long-term living benefit contract.2. Limitations of Mr. Maruf's Term Policy:\n\nMr. Maruf opted for a term insurance policy. While it features a low premium, it operates purely as an expense for a temporary risk window. If Mr. Maruf survives the year, the policy terminates, and he receives absolutely zero financial return or savings benefits from the insurance institution. It provides no wealth accumulation or protection after expiration unless renewed with escalating costs.3. Superior Benefits of Mr. Sumon's Endowment Policy:\n\nOn the other hand, Mr. Sumon took out an \"Endowment Life Insurance Policy\" (মেয়াদি জীবন বিমাপত্র), which requires high quarterly premium installments up to a certain term. This structure serves a dual purpose: risk protection and compulsory savings. If Mr. Sumon passes away during the term, his family instantly receives the full sum assured. More importantly, if he survives the term, Mr. Sumon personally receives the entire face value along with accumulated compound bonuses, providing substantial capital for retirement or personal use.4. Conclusion:\n\nIn conclusion, although Mr. Sumon pays a much higher premium rate, his policy acts as a reliable long-term investment vehicle that guarantees a substantial financial return upon survival. Conversely, Mr. Maruf’s cheap policy offers temporary shield only during his high-risk trip, rendering the claim that Mr. Sumon secures far superior financial benefits completely valid."
