                                "id": "fin2-ch11-cq-063",
                                "stem": "Shahrukh lives in the same house with his father. The house is registered in his father's name. Out of concern that the house might be damaged if an earthquake occurs, Mr. Shahrukh went to insure the house, but the insurance company refused to insure it. Then, Mr. Shahrukh's father insured the house himself. Afterward, Mr. Shahrukh finished construction work on the 2nd and 3rd floors of the house without informing the insurance company. Immediately after the construction of the 2nd floor was completed, the house collapsed. When Mr. Shahrukh's father made an insurance claim, the insurance company refused to honor it.",
                                "stemImage": "",
                                "meta": "Mymensingh · 2023",
                                "type": "board",
                                "questions": [
                                        {
                                                "label": "a",
                                                "text": "What is risk?",
                                                "answer": "Risk (ঝুঁকি) is the measurable probability or uncertainty of financial loss, damage, or an unfavorable outcome resulting from an unexpected future event."
                                        },
                                        {
                                                "label": "b",
                                                "text": "An insurance contract is not a wagering contract'—Explain.",
                                                "answer": "An insurance contract is not a wagering (gambling) contract because insurance is legally based on the Principle of Indemnity (ক্ষতিপূরণের নীতি) and protects a genuine financial interest, whereas a wager is a speculative gamble designed purely for profit.In a wagering contract, parties create an artificial risk solely to win money dependent on a random outcome, meaning one party's gain is strictly another's loss. Conversely, an insurance contract aims to restore the insured to the exact financial position they occupied right before an unfortunate, real-world loss occurred, without allowing the policyholder to make any commercial profit from the accident."
                                        },
                                        {
                                                "label": "c",
                                                "text": "Due to which principle did the insurance company disagree with Mr. Shahrukh's proposal? Explain.",
                                                "answer": "The insurance company did not agree to Mr. Shahrukh's proposal due to the violation of the \"Principle of Insurable Interest\" (বিমাযোগ্য স্বার্থের নীতি).According to insurance laws and statutory regulations, insurable interest refers to the legal right or financial relationship that a policyholder must have with the subject matter of insurance. Under this mandatory principle, the person taking out the policy must stand to benefit directly from the asset's safety and suffer an immediate financial loss from its damage or destruction.In the given stem, the house is legally registered in Shahrukh's father's name, making the father the sole legal proprietor of the property. Although Shahrukh resides in the same house, he holds no legal ownership or direct financial title over the structure. Since Shahrukh does not possess a legally recognized insurable interest in his father's asset, the insurance provider rightfully refused his proposal to execute a contract."
                                        },
                                        {
                                                "label": "d",
                                                "text": "Is Mr. Shahrukh's father eligible to receive the insurance claim in light of the stem? Give your opinion.",
                                                "answer": "1. Evaluation of Claim Eligibility:\n\nNo, Mr. Shahrukh's father is not eligible to receive the insurance claim, and the insurance company’s decision to refuse the payout is completely logical, legally valid, and strictly aligned with general insurance regulations.2. Violation of the Principle of Utmost Good Faith:\n\nGeneral insurance contracts (such as property or fire policies) are strictly bound by the Principle of Utmost Good Faith (চূড়ান্ত সদ্বিশ্বাসের নীতি). This rule dictates that both parties must transparently disclose all material facts regarding the asset. Crucially, the insured is contractually obligated to instantly inform the insurer about any material alterations that significantly increase the physical risk profile of the property during the active term of the policy.3. Material Change in Risk Profile:\n\nThe stem notes that after the father took out the policy, Mr. Shahrukh finished construction work on the 2nd and 3rd floors without informing the insurance company (বিমা কোম্পানিকে না জানিয়ে). Adding multiple structural stories to an existing building drastically changes its structural weight and risk environment. By failing to report this major structural expansion, the insured actively concealed a material change in risk, which directly caused the subsequent collapse of the structure. Under insurance law, concealing material risk variations breaches the contract and instantly voids the insurer’s liability.4. Conclusion:\n\nIn conclusion, because the structural expansion was carried out clandestinely without the required engineering re-underwriting or notification to the insurer, the policy became legally invalid. Therefore, Mr. Shahrukh's father has forfeited his right to compensation, and the insurance company acted with absolute legal precision by denying the claim."
