                                                "label": "c",
                                                "text": "What type of insurance policy was adopted by Mr. Ajmal in the stem? Explain.",
                                                "answer": "First Paragraph (Knowledge):\n\nThe insurance policy adopted by Mr. Ajmal in the stem is a Term Life Insurance (মেয়াদি বিমা / সাময়িক বিমা) policy.\n\n\nSecond Paragraph (Understanding):\n\nTerm life insurance is a type of life insurance policy that provides coverage for a specific, temporary period (such as 1 year, 5 years, etc.). Under this contract, the sum assured is payable to the beneficiaries or nominees only if the insured individual passes away within the specified term. If the insured survives the term, the policy expires, and no money or premium is returned by the insurance company.\n\n\nThird Paragraph (Application):\n\nIn the stem, Mr. Ajmal is going to a war-torn country where high death risks exist. To secure his children's financial future during this dangerous period, he purchases a 1-year temporary policy. The contract explicitly dictates that his children will receive the insurance claim only if he dies within that 1 year. Since the coverage is strictly limited to a specific time frame and pays out only upon death within that period, it perfectly aligns with the characteristics of Term Life Insurance."
