                                                "answer": "First Paragraph (Cognitive):\n\nReinsurance is a process where an insurance company transfers a portion of its undertaken financial risks to another insurance company to protect itself from potentially catastrophic losses.\n\n\nSecond Paragraph (Analytical):\n\nWhen an insurance company accepts a high-value policy that exceeds its financial capacity, it retains a manageable portion of the risk and insures the remaining excess amount with another larger insurer (the reinsurer). In this arrangement, the primary insurance company pays a premium to the reinsurer, and if a massive claim arises, the reinsurer shares the financial burden proportionally, thereby stabilizing the primary insurer's solvency."
